          "54 international students",
          "1 Physics Laboratory",
          "LMS logs",
          "None Specified",
          "[Accesses to platform, Video tutorials watched, video viewing frequency, Videos watched, Display Frequency of Video Experiments, Assignment completion]",
          "The authors condensed the logs into features - video watches have been aggregated. \n\nData was normalized.",
          "k-Means, Mean-Shif, Hierarchical Clustering, DBSCAN, GMM, SOM",
          "{Silhouette Score: 0.644 - k-Means} ",
          "3",
          "Cluster 0 - Students with low activity on the platform: Lowest average grade (53/100)\n\nCluster 1 - Average Activity on the platform: 2nd highest average grade (72.04)\n\nCluster 3 - Very Active Students who completed all assignments. Highest average grade: 82.5\n\n",
          "Authors subscribe to the school of heterogenous groups being better than homogenous groups. \n\nMore engagement seems to correlate well with performance.\n",
          "Authors perform a 2-step study:\n\n1. Comparison of clustering approaches to select the best clustering algorithm.\n\n2. Formation of heterogenous groups using the clustering results. \n\nAuthors find k-means with 3 groups to be the best algorithm for this task. Cluster interpretation is consistent with literature: more engagement leads to better performance overall.",
          "Does not showcase results from the group formation.\n\nSmall sample size.\n\nOnline only context"
        ]
      ],
